    <h1  style="text-align: center;">Sustainable Schools</h1>
    <h2  style=" text-align: left;"><br>
    </h2>
    The three schools in the sustainable schools group are working together to share ideas, resources, and effort across a number of aspects of sustainability.
     
   <h3  style=" text-align: left;">Initially we are looking into:</h3>
    
    <ul>
<li>Energy</li>
<li>Transport</li>
<li>Waste/Recycling</li>
</ul>
    
    Schools are in a unique position because not only are they relatively large enterprises in their own right, they also 
    can have a significant ongoing effect as "learning labs for sustainable
    development, where young students are being prepared to adapt to and help
    mitigate the consequences of climate change.‚Äù World Economic Forum 2015
  
   <h3  style=" text-align: left;">The schools involved are:</h3>
  
      <ul>
      <li><span>Rednock,</span></li>
      <li><span>Archway,</span></li>
      <li><span>Thomas Keble and</span></li>
      <li><span>Maidenhill</span></li>
    </ul>  
    

